Ozophores relatively conical, of type III sensu Juberthie (1970) (Figs 7A, 9A). Coxae of legs I and II mobile, coxae of remaining legs fixed. Male coxae II-IV meeting in the midline (Fig. 7B). Male gonostome small, subtriangular, wider than long (Fig. 7B). Spiracles circular and C-shaped with slightly recurved edges (Fig. 9), as found in "open circle" type of Giribet and Boyer (2002) . Anal region of "pettalid type" (
Giribet and Boyer 2002
). Anal plate convex and granulated (Fig. 8B). Short, round scopula extruding from posterior third of anal plate and extending just past posterior margin of anal plate (Fig. 8B). Orientation of scopula obscures anal pores, which are not visible (Fig. 8B).

